The pattern underneath (clean version)

Think of it like this:

1) Signal → Frame → Interpretation → Action → Feedback
	•	Signal: what’s said (words, tone, symbols, timing)
	•	Frame: how it’s presented (fear, opportunity, identity, etc.)
	•	Interpretation: how the receiver maps it to their world
	•	Action: what they do next
	•	Feedback: results reinforce or reshape the next signal

That loop runs everywhere:
	•	marketing
	•	politics
	•	social media
	•	everyday conversations

